A man has been shot dead in what is alleged to be an attempted hijacking on Henderson Road in Pinetown, West of Durban, on Thursday. According to Shawn Herbst of Netcare 911, the driver of the car had been shot and was found in critical condition inside the car. “Due to the nature of the man’s injuries, the Netcare helicopter ambulance was at the scene. A full advanced life support resuscitation was initiated however, the man’s condition rapidly deteriorated,” said Herbst. The circumstances leading up to the incident will be investigated by the Pinetown SAPS who were on scene.